  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0d9a \u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0ddd \u0d85\u0dc3\u0db1\u0dd3\u0db4 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dcf: \u0d9c\u0db8\u0dca\u0db4\u0dc4 \u0dbb\u0ddd\u0dc4\u0dbd \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db3\u0da7\u0db8 \u0dbd\u0dd9\u0da9\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Employees are sick: Gampaha Hospital is getting very sick",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the sources of the hospital, the work of the Gampaha District General Hospital has been almost completely disrupted due to the non-reporting of the nursing staff and junior staff in several departments on sick leave since yesterday (2).",
        "Commenting on this matter, the Secretary of the Gampaha Hospital Branch of the Government Nurses Association said that such a step had to be taken against the cancellation of the two days a week special leave given to the staff of several departments including the nursing staff by the State Administration Circular No. 15 / 2022 on 15th June last. Hemakanti Attanayake said that the special leave given in other hospitals has been suspended only in Gampaha Hospital.",
        "The secretary stated that despite the discussion with the hospital director since the 19th regarding the cancellation of the special leave granted due to the difficulty of reporting to work amid the ongoing fuel crisis and transportation difficulties, no solution was found and the union has taken a decision not to report to work until a solution is found. .",
        "Gampaha Hospital Branch President of the Republic of Sri Lanka Health Services Association R. KP Mr. Ratnayake said that the discussion held yesterday morning to find a solution to this also failed.",
        "It has been learned that due to this trade union action, the hospital is unable to maintain outpatient treatment activities, ambulance services, food supply to inpatients and even emergency treatment activities.",
        "Regarding the current situation, Gampaha Hospital Director Dr. Saman Pathirana stated that he was unable to provide a solution regarding the cancellation of the special leave through a circular and that despite informing the staff about this, the Ministry of Health of the Western Province did not accept it. That they have asked for advice from the Gampaha District Health Services Director."
      ],
